You will support the calculation and evaluation of fund performance, collaborate with internal stakeholders to deliver effective solutions, and identify operational risks to strengthen the internal control environment.

Your Key Responsibilities:

Ensure the integrity and timeliness of daily and monthly end unit pricing calculated by the custodian.
Conduct benchmarking, attribution analysis, and tolerance checking of portfolios.
Assist in verifying the accuracy of performance reporting provided by custodians.
Collate performance, attribution, and management reports for key stakeholders.
Support the implementation of systems that enhance internal performance and attribution calculations.
Proactively review processes to identify and implement efficiency improvements.
Lead or support projects within Investment Operations as required.

To be successful, you will need

Tertiary qualifications in Business, Accounting, Finance, or a related discipline.
3+ years' experience in Superannuation or Investment Management.
Demonstrated experience in Unit Pricing or Fund Accounting (essential).
Exposure to performance and attribution analysis within Superannuation, Funds Management, or Custodial Services (beneficial).
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a high attention to detail.
Proven ability to meet deadlines and manage competing priorities under pressure.
Advanced Excel skills required; experience with VBA or SQL scripting desirable.
Experience with Bloomberg, FactSet, and Private i platforms advantageous.
Progress toward CA, CPA, CFA, or CIPM qualifications will be well regarded.

If this role aligns with your skills/experience and you are looking for your next opportunity, apply now! For further information, please reach out to Peter via email (Peter.Li@talentinternational.com)

Job Title: Senior Enterprise Strategy and Continuous Improvement Specialist (CI Focus)
Category:
Other (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Shape enterprise continuous improvement at one of Australia's most iconic institutions
Newly created permanent position
Sydney-based hybrid work environment


ABOUT THE TEAM

The Enterprise Strategy and Change Department enables the Reserve Bank of Australia to deliver on its Corporate Plan by coordinating enterprise strategic planning, governing the enterprise project portfolio, delivering IT-enabled change, and embedding a continuous improvement (CI) capability.


As part of this department, the Strategy & Continuous Improvement team plays a central role in shaping the Bank's strategic direction and driving operational excellence. This newly created role will report to the Manager - Continuous Improvement, and work closely with the Manager - Strategic Planning to support enterprise-wide initiatives. While the primary focus of this role is on enterprise continuous improvement, the role will flex to support strategic planning and execution efforts as needed, ensuring balanced delivery across the broader team.


ABOUT THE ROLE
As a Senior Strategy and Continuous Improvement Specialist (Continuous Improvement focus), you will:


Lead enterprise continuous improvement capability development, partnering with senior leaders and business units to shape and execute enterprise-wide continuous improvement initiatives, embed improvement practices that enhance efficiency and effectiveness, while aligning with the Bank's strategic priorities.
Design and evolve the Bank's enterprise CI frameworks and systems, ensuring robust governance, performance alignment, and integration with strategic planning processes.
Conduct structured analysis and process reviews to identify improvement opportunities, validate hypotheses, and inform decisions that support both operational excellence and strategic outcomes.
Facilitate CI workshops, problem-solving sessions, and capability uplift programs across the organisation to build a culture of continuous improvement that complements strategic objectives.
Develop innovative CI solutions to address complex organisational challenges, ensuring they deliver measurable impact and support long-term strategic direction.
Collaborate with the enterprise strategy team as needed to ensure improvement initiatives are prioritised and aligned with enterprise strategy.
Engage executives, committees, and governance bodies through clear communication and compelling storytelling that demonstrates the value of CI in achieving strategic goals.
Help build a high-performing, values-led CI function that drives operational excellence, fosters alignment, and amplifies enterprise impact.


ABOUT YOU
You are a collaborative problem solver and improvement champion with a passion for driving operational excellence and meaningful change. You bring:


Experience & Expertise

6 to 8+ years' experience in continuous improvement, process optimisation, and transformation within large, complex institutions, with exposure to strategic alignment.
Minimum 5 years in a CI / operational excellence or consulting role at Manager level or equivalent (e.g., Big Four, Tier 1.5, MBB); strong improvement and consulting toolkit (very highly regarded).
Experience in financial services or public sector environments (highly regarded).
Strong analytical and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to shape enterprise CI frameworks, apply proven methodologies, map processes, identify improvement opportunities, and design performance and benefit realisation models that quantify, forecast, and link initiatives to strategic outcomes.
Experience designing and applying organisational value chains to identify improvement opportunities, drive measurable benefits, and enable strategic impact at scale (highly regarded).
Proven ability to translate improvement opportunities into actionable plans and measurable benefits, aligned with enterprise strategy.
Experience supporting executive-level engagements and enterprise-wide improvement initiatives, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities.



Skills & Capabilities

Proficient at synthesising a variety of information and data into insights, options, and recommendations.
Excellent communication skills (verbal, written, and visual) with the ability to influence and engage across all levels.
Strong workshop design and facilitation skills (e.g. framework & methodology / strategy / program & opportunity co-design, strategic planning, process mapping / improvement, capability uplift).
Ability to work autonomously and collaboratively in a high-performing team.
Comfortable navigating ambiguity, learning and adapting quickly, and delivering results in a dynamic environment.
Understanding of financial services regulation, compliance, and institutional accountability (highly regarded).



Qualifications

Tertiary qualifications in Business, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related discipline.
Postgraduate qualifications, e.g. MBA (highly regarded).
Certifications in Human-Centred Design, Design Thinking, Agile, Lean Six Sigma, Certified Quality Engineer, or Project/Program Management (e.g. PRINCE2, MSP, PMI) are advantageous but not mandatory.



Why Join Us

Purpose-driven work that shapes the prosperity of Australia.
Opportunity to influence enterprise-wide strategy and transformation in a unique central bank context.
Collaborative, high-integrity culture that values excellence, learning, and inclusion.
Hybrid working model with flexibility to work from home and the office, as agreed with your manager.


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives.


The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Full-time, continuing role

Join a dynamic team driving data innovation

Base salary $126,065 - $142,171 + 17% super




About the opportunity



We're looking for an Analytics Specialist to join our Advanced Analytics, Planning and Enterprise Data team within the Strategy Portfolio. In this pivotal role, you'll turn complex data into clear, actionable insights that shape decisions and enhance the staff and student experience.



You'll work closely with stakeholders across the University to solve real-world challenges using advanced analytics and data visualisation. Your technical expertise and storytelling skills will help bring data to life - making it accessible, governed, and impactful.



This is your chance to collaborate with a passionate analytics community and deepen your understanding of the drivers behind a thriving university environment.



Your key responsibilities will be to:




Design and deliver sustainable analytics solutions using SQL and Python

Translate data into insights and guide stakeholders in data-informed decision-making

Build strong partnerships to apply analytics and machine learning for meaningful impact




About you




Tertiary qualifications in analytics, data, or a related field (or equivalent experience)

Strong programming skills in Python and SQL

Proven experience delivering insights with tools like Power BI

Skilled in data validation, pattern recognition, and storytelling with data

Confident presenting to diverse audiences in clear, non-technical language

Experience with machine learning and Snowflake is a plus






Sponsorship / work rights for Australia



You must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this employment to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment.

Your employment is conditional upon the completion of all role required pre-employment or background checks in terms satisfactory to the University. Similarly, your ongoing employment is conditional upon the satisfactory maintenance of all relevant clearances and background check requirements. If you do not meet these conditions, the University may take any necessary step, including the termination of your employment.



EEO statement



At the University of Sydney, our shared values are trust, accountability and excellence and we strive to be a place where everyone can thrive. We are committed to creating a University community that thrives through diversity and reflects the wider community that we serve. We deliver on this through our commitment to diversity and inclusion, evidenced by our people and culture programs, as well as key strategies to increase participation and support the careers of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People, women, people living with a disability, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, and those who identify as LGBTQIA+. We welcome applications from candidates from all backgrounds.



We are proud to be recognised as an Australian Workplace Equality Index (AWEI) Platinum Employer. Find out more about our work on diversity and inclusion.

Ad Text:
Job Description

This role is a national position, welcoming applicants from any city in Australia that hosts a KPMG office.

KPMG’s Technology Implementation team supports clients across a range of industries to deliver technology enabled business transformation. Our unique business driven approach provides requires deep industry insight, functional expertise and technology know-how that underpins an organisation’s strategic goals

Our SAP Capability team is growing nationally, and in this position, you will be a vital member of our team of SAP analysts and functional consultants. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in SAP Financials with specific expertise in S/4HANA implementations. This role will involve working closely with clients to understand their financial processes, assist in architecting solutions, and contribute to project success.

Key Responsibilities

The successful candidate will play a crucial role by:

Solution Design & Configuration:

Support requirement gathering, process analysis, and design workshops with clients.

Provide support and expertise in the configuration, customization, and enhancement of SAP FI (General Ledger, Accounts Payable, Accounts Receivable, Asset Accounting, Bank Accounting) and CO (Cost Center Accounting, Profit Center Accounting, Internal Orders, Product Costing, Profitability Analysis) modules to meet business needs.

Contribute to the development of functional specifications and system configurations to meet client needs.

Project Assistance:

Support project planning, scheduling, and execution.

Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to ensure cohesive project delivery.

Assist in managing project risks and issues and implement mitigation strategies.

Business Process Optimization:

Partner with finance teams to analyze existing processes, identify gaps, and recommend best practices using SAP capabilities to enhance efficiency and compliance.

Integration Management:

Ensure seamless integration of SAP FI/CO with other modules (e.g., MM, SD, PP) and external systems, maintaining data integrity and consistency.

Stakeholder Engagement:

Act as a liaison between finance business units and IT, translating business requirements into technical specifications and ensuring alignment with strategic objectives.

Serve as a contact for clients within your area of responsibility.

Help build and maintain strong relationships with stakeholders.

Ensure client satisfaction by delivering high-quality support and services.

Support & Troubleshooting:

Provide expert-level support for SAP FI/CO issues, including month-end/year-end closings, financial reporting, and system troubleshooting.

Share knowledge and assist in mentoring junior team members.

Training & Documentation:

Assist in developing training materials, conduct user training sessions, and maintain comprehensive documentation for configurations, processes, and procedures.

Innovation:  

Stay updated on SAP advancements (e.g., S/4HANA) and finance technology trends.

Recommend upgrades or new functionalities to enhance financial operations.

Identify opportunities for process optimisation within client environments

How are you Extraordinary?

You are able to quickly build strong relationships and network with a variety of stakeholders both internal and external.

You are passionate about the importance of fantastic communication to share ideas, inspire, and create change. You are able to digest, distil, and communicate complex concepts in both written and verbal forms.

You are a kind and compassionate with a passion for continually growing your skills.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and unique experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients and communities.
To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills & experience could include: 

A minimum of 3-5 years’ experience in SAP Finance implementations in a consulting or similar external client facing role.

Experience in at least one full lifecycle SAP S/4HANA implementation is preferred

Strong understanding of finance and accounting principles.

Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills.

Ability to work independently and as part of a team.

Strong functional experience of SAP S/4 Hana Finance and Controlling in at least one of the following functional areas:

Finance GL, AR, AP, Fixed Assets

Treasury Management

Group Reporting

Management Accounting (Cost Controlling)

Margin analysis 

Product Costing 

Qualifications

Tertiary qualification (Masters or Bachelor’s degree) in a relevant field.

Current SAP S/4HANA  Certifications.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

You will work closely with business stakeholders, architects, and technical teams to deliver scalable, high-performance reporting solutions using tools such as SAP Analytics Cloud (SAC), SAP Datasphere, and S/4HANA Embedded Analytics.

Job Title: Project Manager – Microsoft Cloud & Data Projects - Remote
Ad Text:
Project Manager – Microsoft Cloud & Data Projects

Australia-wide | Permanent Full-time, Contract and Casual positions

Lead delivery across AI, Data & Integration initiatives for top-tier clients

About Agile Insights

Agile Insights is one of Australia’s fastest-growing Microsoft Data & AI consulting firms. We work with government and enterprise clients to design and deliver modern data platforms, AI solutions, and cloud transformations using Fabric, Azure, Power Platform and OpenAI. As a Microsoft Solutions Partner with Advanced Specialisation in AI, we’re trusted by Microsoft, and referred into some of the most interesting projects in market. Our delivery team is growing and we’re now looking for an experienced Project Manager to lead key engagements and help uplift delivery maturity across the business.

About the Role

We are seeking an exceptional Project Manager to join our Project Management Office and lead the successful delivery of complex, high-impact technology projects. This role demands a results-oriented professional with strong command over cost and budget management, delivery excellence, and a proven track record of driving outcomes in fast-paced, high-stakes environments. You will serve as Project Manager for select large-scale client engagements, taking full ownership of end-to-end Project including financials, timelines, deliverables and outcomes. Beyond execution, you will contribute in scaling processes and enabling organizational growth through disciplined execution and strategic stakeholder engagement. Hands-on experience in AI and Data Engineering projects is highly valued and will position you as a strategic asset to our advanced technology initiatives.

Key Responsibilities

1. Delivery & Financial Management

Own end-to-end delivery of complex technical projects spanning Azure cloud, data platforms, AI solutions, and enterprise integration initiatives
Develop and manage comprehensive delivery plans, including detailed budgets, resource allocation, timelines, and financial forecasts
Drive cost-effective delivery outcomes by optimizing resource utilization, identifying cost-saving opportunities, and maintaining strict budget adherence
Conduct regular budget reviews with stakeholders, providing clear financial reporting, variance analysis, and actionable insights
Proactively manage risk, scope, and change with particular focus on financial implications and delivery impact
Manage change requests with strict adherence to financial impact assessment and approval protocols, ensuring all variations are properly documented and authorized

2. Stakeholder & Client Management

Work closely with clients, internal consulting teams, and Microsoft to ensure project success and client satisfaction
Manage multi-stakeholder engagements across technical and business domains, navigating ambiguity and organizational change
Communicate confidently and effectively with engineers, business users, and C-level stakeholders
Build and maintain strong client relationships while managing expectations around scope, budget, and delivery timelines

3. Team Leadership & Capability Building

Lead and mentor Agile delivery squads, fostering high-performance team culture
Influence and evolve internal delivery frameworks, methodologies, and best practices
Contribute to the internal PMO capability uplift through development of templates, processes, and delivery standards
Share knowledge and lessons learned to strengthen organizational project delivery maturity

Essential Requirements

Have 5+ years’ experience delivering technical projects in consulting (Microsoft, Databricks, AWS etc)
Strong understanding of both Agile and Waterfall/hybrid delivery frameworks with demonstrated ability to apply the right approach for each context
Proven track record of delivering projects on time and within budget in fast-paced, dynamic environments and can build structure quickly and adapt plans in fast-paced environments
Are comfortable managing scope, change and risk in high-value, multi-party projects
Communicate confidently with engineers, business users, and C-level stakeholders
Are looking to make a real impact inside a high-performance, growth-minded firm

Core Competencies

Financial acumen: Demonstrated ability to build, manage, and report on project budgets with accuracy and transparency
Delivery excellence: Can build project structure quickly and adapt plans in response to changing requirements or constraints
Risk & change management: Comfortable managing scope, change, and risk in high-value, multi-party projects with competing priorities
Stakeholder management: Excellent communication and influencing skills across all organizational levels, from technical teams to executive leadership
Problem-solving: Ability to navigate ambiguity, remove blockers, and find pragmatic solutions to complex delivery challenges

What We're Looking For

A delivery-focused professional who takes ownership of outcomes, not just outputs
Someone who understands that budget management is as critical as technical delivery
A structured thinker who can balance planning rigor with adaptive flexibility
A natural communicator who can translate technical complexity into business value
A collaborative leader who elevates team capability while driving results
Someone looking to make a real impact inside a high-performance, growth-minded consulting firm

What’s In It for You?

At Agile Insights, we believe in nurturing talent and creating a supportive, flexible, and rewarding workplace. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Wellbeing: Access to hybrid work arrangements, an Employee Assistance Program, and an individualised gym and wellbeing program.
Flexibility: Work from anywhere for up to 6 weeks per year.
Professional Development: Additional paid leave for certifications and exams, with Agile-sponsored training programs for Microsoft and Databricks certifications.
Team Engagement: Enjoy regular team meetups, including state-based gatherings and an annual all-company event.
Equipment & Hardware: Receive an allowance for your home office setup and a 2-year equipment incentive.
Salary Packaging: Access novated leasing services for tax-effective car purchases.
Learning Resources: Expand your skills with access to our digital library and learning platforms.
Opportunity to work with some of the best developers in the business including one on one mentoring with senior consultants.

Why Agile Insights?

Work with some of the largest clients and global brands across diverse industries.
Be part of a fast-growing, award-winning team passionate about transforming organisations with Data & AI.
Thrive in a friendly start-up culture that values innovation, collaboration, and work-life balance.

Ready to Lead with Us?

If you’re passionate about analytics, consulting, and community engagement, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join Agile Insights and take your career to the next level!

No Agencies - No overseas applications - Must be in Australia and have full work rights

Drive innovation and process improvement across a strategic platform

About us

The NSW Police Force (NSWPF) is one of the largest police forces in the western world, with more than 20,000 employees, including more than 4,000 administrative employees who support the sworn officers that provide a range of law and order services 24 hours a day, seven days a week to the socially, geographically and culturally diverse community of NSW.

About the role

We have an opportunity for a Manager - Strategic Intelligence & Policy to be part of our State Intelligence Command. The Manager - Strategic Intelligence and Policy provides high-level strategic and policy advice to ensure senior decision makers are informed on emerging crime and law enforcement trends and issues. The position also leads and manages the delivery of strategic intelligence reporting, targeting, and policy to provide complex strategic analysis and make high-level recommendations for consideration by the senior NSWPF executive. Through the provision of high level advice and support to the Director, Strategic Intelligence and Capability, the Manager - Strategic Intelligence and Policy ensures NSWPF intelligence is informed and influential on committees and partnerships with other law enforcement and intelligence agencies.

A requirement of this role is to obtain and maintain a Negative Vetting Level 1 (NV1) National Security Clearance within 12 months of commencement in the role.

View the relevant role description  for more information on this role (e.g. essential requirements, key accountabilities, key challenges and capabilities required for the role)

What we can offer you

competitive salary;

flexible work options;

opportunity to purchase leave;

annual leave loading;

corporate wellbeing programs including seminars and the Fitness Passport;

free annual influenza vaccination;

salary packaging options via superannuation contributions or a novated vehicle lease;

How to Apply

Applications can only be submitted electronically via the I Work for NSW website.

To be considered for this role, attach a cover letter (2 pages maximum) and an up-to-date resume that clearly details your skills & experience as relevant to this role.

Please do not attach copies of qualifications, certificates or documentation (other than what has been requested) - you can bring these if called for interview.

Please address each of the following Target Questions (500 word per question) in the text boxes provided in the online application or attach as a separate document.

Target Question 1:

Describe a time you have used high level analytical skills in the production of research/intelligence reports which also had operational and/or tactical outcomes. How did you manage this process and apply these skills? What was the outcome?


Target Question 2:

Describe a time you have led and managed a team to prepare a briefing or report on an organisational issue. What leadership qualities did you use and how did you apply management principles to achieve the outcome?

Your application must stand on its own merits, and the completeness and relevance of your application will determine if you proceed through to the selection process. 

If you require any further information about this opportunity, please contact the hiring manager Superintendent Stephen Egginton via (02) 8835 9621.

To be eligible to apply for this role, you must meet one of the following statuses:

At Healius, we all have one thing in common, we are passionate about making a difference to the health of Australians. And right now, it's a pretty exciting time to join us, as we transform into a stronger, more agile organisation focused on creating excellent customer and patient experiences, smarter ways of working and building a great place to work.

As part of this transformation, Healius is reimagining healthcare through digital innovation, data intelligence and customer-centric design. The diagnostics industry is evolving rapidly, and we are investing in advanced clinical systems, AI-driven insights and cloud-based platforms to improve the diagnostics journey for patients, doctors and ologists.

This role offers the opportunity to lead enterprise-wide data initiatives that will shape the future of healthcare delivery. You will join a collaborative and forward-thinking team, working with emerging technologies to drive meaningful change in a flexible, purpose-driven environment.

About Us

Healius employs 8,000+ passionate people, with an expansive network of over 100 medical laboratories and 2000 patient collection centres operating across metropolitan, regional and remote Australia.

We provide 1 in every 3 pathology services in Australia, extending from exclusively servicing some of Australia's largest and most complex private and public hospitals, to small Indigenous Australian communities.

This means that you will be working with purpose whilst being a part of a business big enough to offer interstate mobility, job security and opportunities to fulfill your career ambitions.

What You Will Be Doing

As Head of Data, you will play a pivotal role in enabling trusted, connected, and intelligent use of data across all business domains. You will help unlock the full potential of clinical systems, digital experiences, and AI-driven decision-making. Leading a high-performing team, you will embed a culture of data excellence while driving innovation across Healius' digital transformation journey.

Key responsibilities include, but are not limited to, the following:

Define and lead the enterprise data strategy, aligned to Healius' broader transformation roadmap
Design and optimise a cloud-native data platform using Snowflake, Informatica, and Azure Data Factory
Enable natural-language data interactions and AI-assisted analytics via Snowflake Cortex Agent and Analyst
Establish enterprise-wide data architecture, governance, and quality frameworks
Deliver master data management capabilities to support trusted, reusable data assets
Partner with analytics teams to operationalise data for reporting, predictive modelling, and automation
Drive modernisation initiatives, including migration from legacy systems and adoption of APIs, microservices, and event-driven architecture
Champion a data-as-a-product mindset to empower business units with self-service insights
Lead and mentor a national data function, fostering innovation, accountability, and continuous improvement
Provide thought leadership on emerging technologies to keep Healius at the forefront of data and AI innovation

What Type of Person Will Be Successful

We are looking for a strategic and hands-on data leader who thrives in complex environments and is passionate about using technology to drive meaningful change. You will be curious, collaborative and confident in challenging the status quo to deliver smarter, more connected healthcare solutions.

To be successful in this role, you will bring:

Proven experience leading enterprise data transformations in complex environments
Deep technical expertise in Snowflake, including Cortex capabilities
Advanced proficiency with Informatica and Azure Data Factory for ETL/ELT orchestration
Strong understanding of data governance, metadata and master data management
Experience delivering data products and AI-ready datasets for BI, ML and self-service analytics
Familiarity with NoSQL, GraphDB, OLTP and OLAP architectures
Demonstrated success in cloud migration and modernisation initiatives
Strong leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence at all organisational levels.
Proven ability to build and mentor technical teams, driving adoption of best practices and new technologies.
Healthcare industry experience is welcome, but not essential

We believe everyone leads, no matter what role they are in. Our ways of leading are the behaviours that we expect our people to embody and are: Customer Focused, Accountable, Collaborative, Credible & Resourceful.

Benefits, Perks and Wellbeing

As part of working for Healius, you will have access to a range of benefits & perks including:

Benefits platform - Reduce the impact of the cost of living with everyday savings with 500+ of Australia's most-loved brands, (from the weekly grocery shop to premium perks like holidays).
Fitness Passport - Access top fitness centres & pools across Australia at a subsidised rate.

Career growth and development opportunities with access to a comprehensive library of online courses and learning paths via our e-learning platform.
Confidential health and well-being support through our Employee Assistance Program, available to all employees and their family members.

Our Commitment to Diversity And Inclusion

Healius is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive workplace. We seek to recruit from diverse applicants and create teams with skills, perspectives and experiences that complement each other at work. We welcome suitably qualified applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, socio-cultural background, disability, sexual orientation or gender identity.

Healius is a part of the Commonwealth Government's Veteran Employment Committment (VEC) and has been recognised as a Veteran Employment Supporter. Veterans and candidates with Australian Defence Force (ADF) experience are encouraged to apply.

Job Summary

Use your data skills to drive real community impact in a collaborative, values-driven team while growing in analytics, BI, and data strategy.

 

About 

Join a community-focused organisation that’s using data to drive better decisions and deliver more effective services. It’s a place where people care about the “why” behind the numbers, and where data is used to understand people and improve outcomes, not just to report on them.

You’ll be part of a close-knit team that values collaboration, curiosity, and practical problem solving. They’re connecting systems, improving data quality, and turning insights into actions that genuinely help the business and community.

 

The Opportunity

You’ll join a small, collaborative analytics function reporting into the Manager of Applications. The team is responsible for building a single-client view, improving data quality across multiple systems, and turning operational data into insight that program teams and leaders can act on.

This role suits someone with hands-on experience working with data, someone who has tackled challenging datasets, uncovered insights from imperfect sources, and can work closely with service teams to communicate findings clearly and effectively.

 

What You'll Do

In this role, you’ll translate complex data into actionable insights, support decision-making across the organisation, and work closely with teams to ensure information is accurate, meaningful, and accessible. Your work will combine hands-on analysis with stakeholder collaboration to make data genuinely useful.

Design, build and maintain dashboards and visualisations (Power BI).
Write and optimise SQL for reporting, extraction and transformation.
Pull together data from multiple enterprise systems (Dynamics 365, CRM, HRIS, Payroll, etc.) to support a single client view.
Investigate and improve data quality, validation, cleansing and documentation.
Translate business questions into clear metrics, insights and simple stories for non-technical teams.
Work with IT/engineering teams to support integration and automation of reporting workflows.
Provide guidance and training so teams can use self-service BI effectively.
Contribute to data governance, privacy and compliance practices.
 

What You'll Bring

You’ll bring strong analytical skills and a collaborative, solution-focused approach. The right person can work with complex datasets, communicate insights clearly, and support teams in making informed decisions.

Tertiary qualification in a relevant field (Data Analytics, IS, Computer Science or equivalent experience).
Practical Power BI experience (dashboard design, modelling, DAX).
Strong SQL skills across relational databases.
Experience analysing and joining data from multiple enterprise systems (Dynamics 365, CRM, HRIS, Payroll).
Understanding of data integration / ETL patterns and data quality techniques.
Ability to explain technical findings simply and tell the story behind the numbers.
Collaborative, empathetic approach, works well with program teams and stakeholders.
Curious, problem-solving mindset with a genuine interest in using data for impact.
 

Desirable

Familiarity with Microsoft Azure data services (Data Factory, Synapse).

Knowledge of Power Platform / CDS / Dynamics 365 data architecture.

Experience automating workflows and reporting.

Basic exposure to R/Python or predictive techniques.

Power BI / SQL Server certifications.

 

Why Join Us

Be part of a team where your work directly contributes to better outcomes for the community. You’ll join a collaborative, values-driven environment that encourages curiosity, problem-solving, and continuous learning. The role offers the chance to develop your skills in analytics, BI, and data strategy while seeing the real-world impact of your work.

 

Not sure if you meet these requirements? Please apply — we are happy to discuss your individual circumstances.

Why your role matters

The Head of Analytics (Student Experience) is a newly established position within the Division of Education and Student Experience, responsible for creating a centralised analytics function and centre of excellence. This role provides strategic leadership and oversight of divisional data and analytics initiatives that enable evidence-based decision-making and continuous improvement.

The position will design and implement robust frameworks for data analysis and visualisation to generate actionable insights that enhance student experience, performance, satisfaction, engagement, and operational effectiveness. It will also lead the development of a cohesive and strategic approach to business intelligence, promoting a data-informed culture and driving innovation in analytics and insights across the Division.

The Head of Analytics (Student Experience) will collaborate with senior stakeholders across Faculties, Schools, and Divisions to influence strategic direction and shape initiatives that improve the UNSW student experience. The role will work closely with existing data and analytics functions across the University, including University Performance and Planning, the DVC Academic Quality Educational Insights team, the Chief Data Officer, and the Learning Analytics team within the PVCE portfolio.

This position reports to the Director of Operations and will manage a team of direct reports.

Specific accountabilities for this role include:  

Establish and centralised student experience analytics function and centre of excellence, building foundational capabilities and long-term vision.
Lead and develop a high-performing analytics team, fostering innovation and professional growth.
Develop and implement rigorous processes for the analysis and insights of divisional student experience data.
Translate complex data and insights into compelling visual narratives, reports, papers and/or dashboards for leadership and operational teams.
Drive a data-informed culture across the division, promoting evidence-based practice and continuous improvement.

About You:  

A degree in a relevant field such as data science, statistics, computer science, or a related discipline, or equivalent competence gained through any combination of education, training and extensive experience.
Proven experience in data analysis, preferably in higher education or customer experience, and demonstrated ability to translate complex data into actionable insights and compelling visual narratives.
Proficiency in data management, statistical analysis tools, and familiarity with current coding techniques and approaches.
Exceptional verbal and written communication, research, and problem-solving skills. including strong report writing and documentation skills and demonstrated ability to summarise complex material effectively and present key issues for a wide range of audiences.
Strong leadership and people management skills, with demonstrated success in developing and motivating teams.
Detail-oriented with a commitment to ensuring data accuracy, reliability and security. • Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, collaborative environment while managing multiple priorities.
High-level interpersonal and negotiation skills with the ability to build and maintain effective collaborative professional relationships with senior University staff and external stakeholders.
Familiarity with qualitative and quantitative research methods and analysis techniques is advantageous.
An understanding of issues relating to educational quality in tertiary education is advantageous

For further details on role responsibilities and skills & experience required, refer to the position description found under the position listing on Jobs@UNSW

Benefits and Culture:

People are at the core of everything we do. We recognise it is the contributions of our staff who make UNSW one of the best universities in Australia and the world.

Our benefits include:

Flexible working options.
Career development opportunities.
17% Superannuation contributions and additional leave loading payments.

Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness).

Ad Text:
ICT Business Analyst

Inland Rail is seeking an ICT Business Analyst to drive the delivery of fit-for-purpose, cost-effective solutions. Acting as a key liaison between business, technical teams, vendors, and stakeholders, you'll define requirements, document processes, support solution design, and assess business impacts to enable strategic program outcomes.

Key responsibilities will include but are not limited to:


Coordinate and facilitate structured focus groups, workshops, and interviews as an input to business analysis activities for requirements elicitation.
Assess and critically analyse information gathered to develop requirements and prepare the relevant documentation according to business analysis principles.
Undertake current and future state business process analysis using BPMN process modelling to determine business requirements, information flows, and process improvements that streamline ICT and deliver benefits for the business.
Facilitate the design of technology solutions by gathering, analysing, and writing business requirements in functional and technical specifications.
Work with internal teams to obtain and document an in-depth understanding of the existing business processes and systems and how these are used.
Provide timely and expert advice regarding business requirements, system requirements, information requirements, business impacts, scope management, and project risks.
Use communication skills to negotiate, establish, and maintain networks and working relationships with team members, clients, and stakeholders.
Complete the testing cycle from documenting the test scripts, executing, documenting defects, and tracking defect's close out to meet business requirements.

About You

To be successful in this role, you will have a minimum of 5 years' experience working in a demanding professional environment with proven capacity to prioritise, multi-task, achieve unit goals, perform, and always work with a customer focused approach.

You will be able to demonstrate

Demonstrated business analysis skills and experience.
Experience in the development of business process, system and data maps and models and producing current and future state analysis.
Skills and experience in the elicitation and documentation of business and system requirements.
Solid understanding of business analysis principles and Agile methodologies, gap analysis, process modelling, data mapping, interface integration, and APIs; demonstrated ability to work in Scrum, Kanban, and other frameworks.
Understanding and application of the Business Analysis Body of Knowledge (BABOK) principles and Prince2 project methodology.
Strong facilitation, negotiation, and engagement skills to support extensive consultation on a diverse variety of considerations.
Experience in writing test cases and performing and co-ordinating testing activities, in particular, User Acceptance Testing (UAT)
Analytical, problem-solving and research skills to develop innovative and cost-effective solutions to complex issues.
Demonstrated experience working in a demanding professional environment with proven capacity to prioritise, multi-task, achieve unit goals, perform, and always work with a customer focused approach
Excellent skills with Microsoft O365 suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Visio) SharePoint and other technologies as required.

Desirable

Experience with Information Management including Engineering Data and Document Control.
PRINCE2, PMBOK, similar project management methodology qualifications.
Experience in software platforms that support large capital construction programs such as Asset and Property Management, Information and Document Management, Environment, Health and Safety, Engineering and Construction, Program and Project Management and Controls, HCM and Procurement.

About Inland Rail

Inland Rail Pty Ltd is delivering a 1,600km freight line that is transforming how goods are moved around Australia. When fully operational, Inland Rail will connect Melbourne to Brisbane via regional Victoria, New South Wales and Queensland. As one of the largest infrastructure projects in Australia, Inland Rail is helping to address the nation's future freight needs and meet the demands of our growing population. Delivering Inland Rail will help shift more goods onto rail which means safer, less congested roads and fewer emissions and a more resilient and sustainable national freight network.

What you'll be joining

You will join one of the largest infrastructure programs in Australia.
This project will generate thousands of jobs and billions of dollars in local investment, boosting regional economies and communities right along the alignment.
Inland Rail is proud to have over 40% female representation and we would like to see these numbers grow.
Inland Rail is an Agile working environment in our State-of-the Art office embracing flexible working conditions.

Our Organisation and Culture

The values that drive us and the work we deliver in the program incorporate Collaboration, Accountability, Respect and Excellence. We welcome like-minded individuals who value our culture.

At Inland Rail, we celebrate, support, and thrive on attracting people from all horizons and walks of life for the benefit of our employees, our program, and our community. Inland Rail is proud to be an equal opportunity and an affirmative action employer. We encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander candidates to submit their details to us.

All employment is decided based on suitability to the role, cultural fit, merit, and business needs.

Apply Now

If this opportunity sounds like the challenge you have been looking for please apply online today.

As part of the application process, you will be required to undergo pre-employment criminal history, reference and medical checks, including drug and alcohol testing. Inland Rail is a drug and alcohol-free working environment.

Please note that applications are reviewed from point of advertising so don't delay your application.

Toyota Finance Australia (TFA) is the country’s largest automotive financier.  Our past gives us credibility and knowledge. But it’s what the future holds, and how we can make the world a better place, that excites us. It’s not just about technology but what it can do for people.
  
In Australia there are two separate businesses: Toyota Motor Corporation Australia (TMCA) and Toyota Finance Australia (TFA).  While we work closely together, TMCA focuses on vehicles and here at Toyota Finance Australia our priority is to provide finance, insurance and fleet management.
  
At TFA we’re committed to empowering our customers to get into their new car and onto the road. 
  
We’re also passionate about, and committed to, our people.  Our philosophy of Here To Move You represents our commitment to not only move our customers, but help our employees grow. 
  
Your success at TFA is important to us, and we pride ourselves on a work culture that supports and rewards people.
  
From partnering with you to support your career growth, to providing you with opportunities to learn, improve, feel engaged and appreciated, we celebrate our people and the difference they bring.
  
We strive to create a workplace that not only gives equal opportunities to people of all backgrounds and abilities but supports them to reach their full potential.
  
We’re working towards a future where we look out for each other and our planet.  Where we enrich lives with the safest and most responsible ways of moving.  This is the kind of tomorrow we’re imagining here at TFA.
  
Join us and help drive the future.
  
This role is based in our Head Office, Grosvenor Place, Sydney.  The office is within walking distance from the train station.  There are plenty of options for lunch and catching up with colleagues or friends after work. 
  
How you'll make an impact
The Data Governance Specialist plays a key role in developing and embedding data governance practices across the organisation to ensure the availability, quality, security, and appropriate use of data. This role is responsible for implementing data policies, frameworks, and standards that support compliance, drive business value, and improve data maturity, and oversight of the data quality process and register. The position works closely with business units, technology teams, data architects, data owners and data stewards to champion good data management practices and uphold data governance principles across the full data lifecycle.
  
Your usual day in the office will include:

Data Governance Framework & Policy Implementation

Roll out and maintain the Enterprise Data Management Framework.
Maintain and contribute to data governance policies, standards, and procedures.
Promote consistent data definitions, rules, and usage standards across systems. 
Compliance, Risk & Privacy Alignment

Collaborate with Risk, Compliance, Legal, and InfoSec to ensure regulatory alignment.
Support audits, privacy impact assessments, and third-party risk evaluations.
Minimise data-related risks through cross-functional collaboration. 
Data Stewardship & Governance Enablement

Facilitate governance forums (e.g., Data Governance Committee, Stewardship Working Group).
Enable and support Data Owners and Stewards, including onboarding and ongoing engagement.
Monitor compliance with governance and quality standards.
Data Quality & Issue Management

Define and apply data quality rules for critical data elements.
Support profiling, monitoring, and remediation of data quality issues.
Maintain and oversee the Data Issue Management Register and related processes. 
Change Management, Communication & Metadata Oversight

Represent data governance in projects and change initiatives.
Promote data governance awareness and training across the organisation.
Develop and maintain metadata standards, dictionaries, and lineage tools
Your attributes

Experience in data governance, data management, or related roles
Sound knowledge of data governance functions, principles, and best practices
Strong understanding of data management frameworks (e.g. DAMA-DMBoK)
Experience working in complex data environments with multiple stakeholders
Knowledge of data quality management, metadata, data lineage, and stewardship models
Familiarity with regulatory and compliance requirements (e.g. Privacy Act, APRA guidelines)
Demonstrable understanding of data governance and cataloguing tools
Desirable:

Experience with data governance or catalogue tools, and data modelling tools (e.g. Purview, Erwin)
Exposure to data platforms, data warehousing, or analytics environment
Understanding of data platforms (e.g. Databricks, Azure ADF)
Working knowledge of data privacy, data security, and risk management practices
Certification in Data Management
Experience in financial services
Life at Toyota & What we offer you

We pride ourselves on a work culture that supports and rewards people. From development programs to recognition programs, we make sure everyone at Toyota Finance Australia lives their best possible life. After all, our people are our greatest assets.

Toyota Australia is well-recognised for offering:

Ad Text:
Our client is looking for a Chief Data Engineer to join their leadership team. The Chief Data Engineer will lead the design, implementation, and governance of enterprise data solutions that support the organization's strategic objectives. This role combines deep technical expertise in data engineering, Informatica, and cloud-based data lakes with strong strategic leadership to shape the company's data roadmap and enable data-driven decision-making across the business.

Responsibilities
Define and execute the organization's data engineering strategy aligned with business and technology goals.
Architect scalable, secure, and high-performance data platforms and pipelines to support analytics, AI, and operational needs.
Develop and maintain enterprise data lake and data warehouse environments (e.g., AWS, Azure, or GCP).
Lead and mentor data engineering teams, setting best practices for data ingestion, transformation, and integration.
Drive the Informatica ecosystem (PowerCenter, IDMC, IICS) for ETL/ELT, data quality, and metadata management.
Partner with data governance and compliance teams to enforce data standards, lineage, and security protocols.
Ensure adherence to regulatory requirements and internal policies (e.g., GDPR, APRA, or ISO standards).
Implement automated data quality frameworks and observability tools.
Collaborate with business, analytics, and IT stakeholders to understand data needs and deliver actionable solutions.
Communicate complex technical concepts to non-technical audiences, enabling informed business decisions.
Build a culture of innovation, data stewardship, and continuous improvement.
Requirements
15+ years of experience in data engineering, with at least 5+ years in a Excutive Manager or Head of-level role.
Proven experience building and managing enterprise data lakes and ETL/ELT pipelines at scale.
Expertise in Informatica tools (PowerCenter, IICS, IDMC, MDM).
Strong hands-on experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP) and modern data lake architectures (Delta Lake, Iceberg, Lakehouse).
Experience defining and executing data strategies, frameworks, and roadmaps for large organizations.
Familiarity with governance, cataloging, and lineage tools (e.g., Collibra, Alation, or Informatica EDC).
Excellent leadership, stakeholder engagement, and communication skills.
Experience working in Banking or financial services.

If you think you have the above skills and experiences, click the 'Apply' button or send your resume to alex.nguyen@talentinternational.com

Position Description: JR-005030 - Data Engineering & Analytics Manager - UOM 10.pdf

The team

In the Digital and Data Division, our focus is on designing, delivering, managing and protecting technology solutions and services that underpin ONI’s day-to-day operations, as well as broader National Intelligence Community initiatives. We also develop solutions for accessing and analysing information and data that contributes to assessments and business intelligence for decision making customers.

We are responsible for delivering stable, reliable, secure, and scalable hybrid cloud and on-premises environments that support the operational and strategic missions of both ONI and the broader NIC. With a healthy appetite to make the most of cutting-edge technology (including AI), the team is at the forefront of technological development, advancement, innovation and transformation. We are also focused on resilience and strengthening ONI’s cyber security posture, including the Australian Cyber Security Centre (ACSC) Essential Eight mitigation strategies.

Who we are looking for

We’re looking for adaptable, collaborative professionals who thrive in a fast-paced, mission-driven environment. You’ll be part of a team that values good culture, curiosity, initiative, and continuous learning.

We value individuals who are:

Clear communicators across technical and non-technical contexts.
Comfortable navigating ambiguity and shifting priorities.
Committed to teamwork, inclusion, and public service.
Motivated to contribute to national intelligence outcomes.
The roles

Technical Specialists are expected to work independently and collaboratively to solve complex technical problems, mentor others, and translate technical concepts for non-technical audiences. You’ll be proactive in staying current with emerging technologies and applying them to secure government systems.

Technical Managers are expected to lead by example – building team capability, managing delivery cycles, and coordinating across stakeholders. You’ll be responsible for the day-to-day operations including planning, communication and engagement, recruitment, budgeting, and agile delivery.

We are looking to fill a range of Technical Specialist and Technical Manager positions across a range of functions such as:

Enterprise Strategy & Architecture

Shape digital strategy and lead enterprise architecture to uplift technical capability, drive transformation, and influence cross-agency technology planning. This position shapes long-term strategic direction, aligns ICT initiatives with organisational goals, and influences cross-agency planning across the NIC.

Networks and Unified Communications

You’ll help deliver secure, resilient and high-performing infrastructure that supports ONI’s hybrid cloud and on-premises environments. This includes maintaining critical network systems and video teleconferencing services to enable seamless, secure communication across ONI and the NIC. You’ll contribute to the design, implementation and support of technologies essential to mission success, while ensuring alignment with national cyber security standards.

Artificial Intelligence, Data Science & Machine Learning

Lead, design and implement AI/ML solutions to enhance ONI’s analytical capabilities. Apply advanced techniques to extract insights from complex data, enabling secure, scalable, and intelligence-driven decision-making across ONI and the NIC.

Cloud & Infrastructure

Design and maintain hybrid cloud environments using automation and Infrastructure as Code, ensuring performance, reliability, and integration across platforms.

Cyber Security

Lead and implement secure system design, incident response, and governance frameworks that protect sensitive environments and meet accreditation standards.

Systems & Platforms

Engineer and manage virtualised infrastructure, enterprise platforms, and core systems to ensure operational stability and scalability across ONI’s technology landscape. Design, build, and manage infrastructure, platforms, applications, and data systems using engineering, DevOps, and automation practices to ensure scalability, reliability, and insight-driven operations.

IT Service Management

Lead and deliver reliable, secure, and user-focused technology services that support ONI’s mission. You’ll manage service operations, drive continuous improvement, and ensure alignment with best-practice frameworks such as ITIL.

Key attributes

To be successful in this role you will need:

Technical Expertise: Demonstrated skills in a nominated technology field, with experience working in secure government environments.
Problem-Solving and Analytical Thinking: Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to resolve issues and provide strategic advice.
Project and Time Management: Ability to set priorities, monitor progress, and deliver outcomes within defined timeframes.
Collaboration and Stakeholder Engagement: Proven ability to work collaboratively and liaise effectively with internal and external stakeholders, clients, and service providers.
Communication and Adaptability: Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with a driven, enthusiastic, and resilient approach to challenges.

Desirable but not essential:

Relevant tertiary qualifications, or relevant industry qualifications.
Extensive professional experience with demonstrated leadership and management capabilities.

For further information about these opportunities and how to apply, please download a candidate information kit from the careers page of ONI's website.

About us

Independent Schools Queensland (ISQ) is the peak body representing Queensland's independent schooling sector. We represent over 200 diverse member schools across Queensland, and these range from small community schools to large Prep to Year 12 schools and cater for families from a variety of social and economic backgrounds. ISQ provides a united and powerful voice representing and promoting the interests of member schools to governments and the wider community, fostering choice in education and protecting the autonomy of independent schools. Our mission is to champion independent education and to support independent schools to serve their communities. ISQ is a non-profit membership organisation with more than 50 years’ experience at the forefront of education innovation.

ISQ has a commitment to reconciliation, and our Reconciliation Action Plan can be viewed on our website.
